Argentine Stocks: Galicia and Mirgor Advance; YPF Retreats

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-03-23T21:32:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-23/argentine-stocks-ledesma-and-ypf-fall-mirgor-sacifia-gains.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 4:01 p.m. New York time.  The Merval Index gained 0.8 percent to 3,348.83.  Grupo Financiero Galicia SA (GGAL)  ,  Argentina ’s largest
consumer lender, rose 1.1 percent to 5.50 pesos. The price of
Argentine sovereign bonds climb today, which signals higher
value for banks’ fixed-income holdings.  Mirgor SACIFIA (MIRG AF) rose 3.5 percent to a record 135
pesos, its fifth day of gains. The Argentine producer of
automobile air conditioning systems may become part of the
Merval index in April, according to a document posted March 21
on the website of Argentina’s Capital Markets Institute, which
calculates the index.  YPF SA (YPFD)  , the unit of  Spain ’s Repsol YPF SA, fell
0.6 percent to 177 pesos, its third day of losses. Repsol said
the price of an offering of stock in its unit was set at $41 per
American depositary receipt. The company also increased the
offering to 26.2 million ADRs.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
 ethomson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  